{"id":"1901.04176","submitter":"Anna Karczewska","authors":"Anna Karczewska and Piotr Rozmej","title":"Remarks on existence/nonexistence of analytic solutions to higher order\n  KdV equations","comments":"7 pages","journal-ref":"Acta Physica Polonica A 136(6) 910-915 (2019)","doi":"10.12693/APhysPolA.136.910","report-no":null,"categories":"math-ph math.MP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this note, we discuss the existence of analytic solutions to the nonlinear\nwave equations of the higher order than the ubiquitous Korteweg-de Vries (KdV)\nequation. First, we recall our recent results which show that the extended KdV\nequation (KdV2), that is, the equation obtained within second-order\nperturbation approach possesses three kinds of analytic solutions. These\nsolutions have the same functional form as the corresponding KdV solutions. We\nshow, however, that the most intriguing multi-soliton solutions, known for the\nKdV equation, do not exist for KdV2. Moreover, we show that for the equations\nobtained in the third order perturbation approach (and then in any higher\norder) analytic solutions in the forms known from KdV theory do not exist.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 Jan 2019 08:16:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-19"}
