 oxygen atoms and the proton\nordering. For temperatures between 400 K and 600 K there are melting-like\ntransitions from a monolayer of ice to a monolayer of liquid water. These\nfirst-order phase transitions have a latent heat between 3.4 and 4.0 kJ/mol.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 Jan 2019 11:13:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-15"}
